.TH "ufs_get_locked_page" 9 "ufs_get_locked_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufs_get_locked_page \- locate, pin and lock a pagecache page, if not exist read it from disk.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct page *" ufs_get_locked_page
.BI "(struct address_space *mapping "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mapping" 12
the address_space to search
.IP "index" 12
the page index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Locates the desired pagecache page, if not exist we'll read it,
locks it, increments its reference
count and returns its address.
